You are here:

Find and Select Flow Resources More Easily in More Elements

With this update, Flow Builder extends enhanced resource selection to Collection Filter, Collection Sort, Decision, Loop, Subflows, Recommendation Assignment, and Orchestration Stages and Steps elements. It’s also available in Actions without custom property editors.

Resources display by labels and icons are more intuitive. A new tooltip provides details like data type and description. This makes it easier to discover needed resources quickly.

Where: Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic in Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions.

Open an existing flow, select an element, click Edit Element, then click in a resource field. Automatic outputs and variables now display with user-friendly labels under elements they’re created in.

Previously, you could search for a screen component by name without drilling into the specific screen. Now, select the screen it was created from first. If unsure, go to the Toolbox, click Manager, search for the screen component, and click  to view its usage in Screen. This change impacts other nested entities like Decision outcomes, Wait events, and Orchestration Steps.

Let us know so we can improve!
